  "texts": [
    "The bubble diagram (Fig. 4) displays the stimuli and learning environment, with the size of the bubbles corresponding to the number of articles in the review.",
    "Our analysis aimed to scrutinize which stimuli are commonly adopted in different learning environments.",
    "Firstly, video footage remains the dominant stimulus across various scenarios, with over half of the studies (141 articles) utilizing video in physical learning settings and 23 studies using video footage to stimulate reflection in digital learning platforms and OMO settings.",
    "However, there is a disparity in the type of videos used in these settings.",
    "Physical learning environments mostly relied on live-action videos that authentically recorded participants' behaviors and interactions (Chan and Yung, 2015; Nyberg and Larsson, 2017), whereas digital learning environments utilized device screen recordings that captured participants' operations on computer-supported learning platforms (Rassaei, 2013; Lee, 2020)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Physical learning environments mostly relied on live-action videos that authentically recorded participants' behaviors and interactions (Chan and Yung, 2015; Nyberg and Larsson, 2017), whereas digital learning environments utilized device screen recordings that captured participants' operations on computer-supported learning platforms (Rassaei, 2013; Lee, 2020)."
